<TITLE> Women's sports association committee dissolved </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 21 (bdnews24.com) - The National Sports Council Monday dissolved the five-year old ad-hoc committee of the National Women's Sports Association and appointed a new ad-hoc committee, asking it to hold the election within next three months. Jute Ministry's deputy secretary Rina Parveen has been appointed general secretary in place of Qumrunnahar Dana. The then four-party coalition government dissolved the elected committee, led by general secretary Ferdousi Khanam, on March 19 in 2003 and appointed a 31-member committee. The new committee also included former fastest women and national awardees Sufia Khatun and Firoza Begum, gymnastic coach Khurshida Akhter Khushi, physical college vice principal Hosne Ara Hasi, former athlete Lubna Mahmud and Hatemun Nahar and Hosne Ara Habib. Mushfeka Ikfat, who was also chief of the dissolved committee, would be acting as president. A circular stated that the new ad-hoc committee would take over charge soon and hand over the responsibility to the elected committee in three months. It also said that the members of the ad-hoc committee would not be eligible for contesting the upcoming election of the National Women's Sports Association. 
